==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erose
<hw>E*rose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>erosus</ets>,
p. p. See <er>Erode</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Irregular or uneven as
if eaten or worn away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Jagged or irregularly toothed, as
if nibbled out or gnawed.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>E*rose"ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erosion</ent>⟦br⟧
